        {{!-- About description --}}
        <div id="aboutDescription" >
            <p class="bodyText">My name is Scott Olthoff (just in case you didn’t see the big title above). I am a VFX artist and video editor from London, Ontario. I am currently in the Interactive Media Design program at Fanshawe College. When I graduate, I am planning to continue my studies in the Visual Effects and Editing program at Fanshawe to further develop my video skills. My goal is to take any video that is handed to me and make it extraordinary.</p>

            <p class="bodyText">I find video editing and visual effects absolutely fascinating. The stories that you can tell, the emotions you can evoke, the excitement you can create. The fact that we are able to seamlessly blend computer generated images with real footage is mind-boggling. </p>

            <p class="bodyText">My dream is to one day create films and/or music videos. To be able to help a story or song come to life would make my world. Music videos like A$AP Rocky’s “Kids Turned Out Fine” video, edited by Will Town with VFX by Mathematic, help to keep me inspired. I hope to one day create a video as visually mesmerizing as that one.</p>
